class Solution:
    def canChange(self, start: str, target: str) -> bool:
        n = len(start)
        i = j = 0
        while i < n or j < n:
            while i < n and start[i] == '_':
                i += 1
            while j < n and target[j] == '_':
                j += 1
            if i == n and j == n:
                return True
            if i == n or j == n:
                return False
            if start[i] != target[j]:
                return False
            if start[i] == 'L' and i < j:
                return False
            if start[i] == 'R' and i > j:
                return False
            i += 1
            j += 1
        return True
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Two-pointer sweep: skip underscores, ensure same non-underscore order, and verify L can only move left (start index ≥ target index) and R can only move right (start index ≤ target index).

